description:
**Location:** internal/services/feed_service.go:432

**Issue:** The feed fetching service disables TLS certificate verification when running on App Engine (GAE_ENV=standard), making the application vulnerable to man-in-the-middle attacks when fetching RSS feeds.

**Code:**
```go
if os.Getenv("GAE_ENV") == "standard" {
    transport.TLSClientConfig = &tls.Config{
        InsecureSkipVerify: true,
    }
}
```

**Risk:** HIGH - Attackers can intercept HTTPS connections and inject malicious content into RSS feeds.

**Recommendation:** Bundle proper CA certificates or use App Engine's default transport instead of disabling verification.
